29/10/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The defence and interior ministers of Albania, Bulgaria, Croatia, Greece, Macedonia, Serbia-Montenegro, Slovenia and Turkey meet on Friday (29 October) at an international conference entitled "NATO, EU and New Global Risks". The event will be opened by NATO Deputy Secretary General Alessandro Minuto Rizzo, who will deliver a report on the Alliance's contribution to global security and stability and the EU's new security role in Southeast Europe. Representatives of the EU, OSCE, the Council of Europe and the Stability Pact are also participating in the forum. (news.bg, Makfax - 29/10/04)
